  "termsAndConditions": "Terms and Conditions",
  "termsAndConditions_title": "CUISINOUS – TERMS & CONDITIONS (MOBILE APP VERSION)",
  "termsAndConditions_intro": "Last updated: 01-01-2026\n\nThese Terms and Conditions (“Terms”) govern your access to and use of the Cuisinous mobile application and related services (the “App”), operated by 9534-9072 Québec Inc., doing business as Cuisinous (“Cuisinous”, “we”, “us”, “our”).\n\nBy creating an account or using the App, you confirm that you have read, understood, and agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the App.",
  "termsAndConditions_section1Title": "1. WHAT CUISINOUS IS",
  "termsAndConditions_section1Body": "Cuisinous is a technology marketplace that connects independent food Vendors with Customers.\n\nCuisinous:\ndoes not prepare, cook, store, inspect, package, transport, or deliver food;\nis not a restaurant, caterer, or food business;\ndoes not supervise or control Vendors or their kitchens;\ndoes not guarantee food quality, safety, legality, or compliance;\nis not an employer, agent, or partner of any Vendor.\n\nAll food transactions are strictly between the Vendor and the Customer.",
  "termsAndConditions_section2Title": "2. ELIGIBILITY & ACCOUNTS",
  "termsAndConditions_section2Body": "To use the App, you must:\nbe 18 years or older;\nhave legal capacity to enter a contract;\nprovide accurate and current information.\n\nYou are responsible for:\nkeeping your login details secure;\nall activity under your account.\n\nNotify us immediately if you suspect unauthorized access.",
  "termsAndConditions_section3Title": "3. VENDORS",
  "termsAndConditions_section3Body": "Vendors are subject to a separate Vendor Agreement.\nIf there is any conflict between these Terms and the Vendor Agreement, the Vendor Agreement prevails.",
  "termsAndConditions_section4Title": "4. FOOD & LEGAL COMPLIANCE",
  "termsAndConditions_section4Body": "Vendors are solely responsible for:\ncomplying with all applicable laws and regulations;\nholding valid permits and certifications (including MAPAQ);\nfood safety, hygiene, labeling, allergens, and ingredient accuracy;\ntheir food products and preparation methods.\n\nCuisinous does not verify or inspect Vendor compliance.\n\nCustomers acknowledge that:\nfood is prepared by independent Vendors;\nfood consumption carries inherent risks;\nCuisinous makes no guarantees regarding food safety or suitability.",
  "termsAndConditions_section5Title": "5. ORDERS, PAYMENTS & FEES",
  "termsAndConditions_section5Body": "Payments are processed by third-party providers.\nCuisinous does not store full payment details.\n\nPlatform fees or commissions may apply and are shown before confirmation.\nPlatform fees are non-refundable unless required by law.\n\nVendors are responsible for all applicable taxes (GST, QST, income tax).",
  "termsAndConditions_section6Title": "6. CANCELLATIONS & REFUNDS",
  "termsAndConditions_section6Body": "Cancellation and refund policies are set by Vendors and applicable law.\nCuisinous may help facilitate communication but is not required to resolve disputes or issue refunds.",
  "termsAndConditions_section7Title": "7. USER CONTENT",
  "termsAndConditions_section7Body": "You keep ownership of your content (photos, menus, reviews, text).\n\nBy posting content, you grant Cuisinous a worldwide, royalty-free license to use it for App operation, promotion, and analytics.\n\nYou confirm that you have the right to post your content.",
  "termsAndConditions_section8Title": "8. PROHIBITED USE",
  "termsAndConditions_section8Body": "You may not:\nbypass the App to transact off-platform;\nprovide false or misleading information;\nviolate laws or third-party rights;\npost harmful, illegal, or deceptive content;\nmisuse the App or harm Cuisinous’ reputation.",
  "termsAndConditions_section9Title": "9. ACCOUNT SUSPENSION OR TERMINATION",
  "termsAndConditions_section9Body": "Cuisinous may, where legally permitted:\nsuspend or terminate accounts;\nremove listings or content;\nrestrict access to the App.\n\nNo compensation is owed unless required by law.",
  "termsAndConditions_section10Title": "10. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY",
  "termsAndConditions_section10Body": "All App content, branding, software, and trademarks belong to Cuisinous or its licensors.\nNo rights are granted except as expressly stated.",
  "termsAndConditions_section11Title": "11. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY",
  "termsAndConditions_section11Body": "To the maximum extent permitted by law, Cuisinous is not liable for:\nfood-related illness, allergies, injuries, or dissatisfaction;\nVendor actions or failures;\nindirect or consequential damages;\nloss of profits, data, or reputation.\n\nNothing limits liability where prohibited by law (e.g. gross negligence).",
  "termsAndConditions_section12Title": "12. INDEMNIFICATION",
  "termsAndConditions_section12Body": "You agree to indemnify and hold harmless Cuisinous from claims arising from:\nyour use of the App;\nfood sold or consumed;\nviolation of these Terms or the law;\ncontent you provide.",
  "termsAndConditions_section13Title": "13. FORCE MAJEURE",
  "termsAndConditions_section13Body": "Cuisinous is not responsible for delays or failures caused by events beyond reasonable control, including natural disasters, government actions, pandemics, or technical failures.",
  "termsAndConditions_section14Title": "14. CHANGES TO TERMS",
  "termsAndConditions_section14Body": "We may update these Terms at any time.\nContinued use of the App means you accept the updated Terms.",
  "termsAndConditions_section15Title": "15. GOVERNING LAW",
  "termsAndConditions_section15Body": "These Terms are governed by the laws of Québec, Canada.",
  "termsAndConditions_section16Title": "16. CONTACT",
  "termsAndConditions_section16Body": "Questions or legal notices: info@cuisinous.ca",
